<subSubSection id="1BD8652DFFF2FFECE24D02D5FC65FCD6" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="537D36A6FFF2FFECE24D02D5FC65FCD6" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">
[TL: 
<collectingCountry id="2BD57636FFF2FFECE28802D5FBBDFD6A" box="[946,1054,655,681]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">Kirghizia</collectingCountry>
, Kirghiz Mts., Ala-Too settlement vicinity, 
<quantity id="943A9B43FFF2FFECE1C302E9FE36FD0E" box="[249,405,690,717]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" unit="m" value="1150.0" valueMax="1200.0" valueMin="1100.0">1100–1200 m</quantity>
] is figured upperside and underside by the authorities (
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFF2FFECE2C502E9FB1EFD0E" author="Korb, S. K. &amp; Stradomsky, B. V. &amp; Kuznetsov, G." box="[1023,1213,690,717]" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" pagination="140 - 145" refId="ref9752" refString="Korb, S. K., Stradomsky, B. V. &amp; Kuznetsov, G. (2015) Two new subspecies of Melitaea ornata Christoph, 1893 (Lepidoptera, Nymphalidae) from Europe and Middle Asia. Amurian zoological journal, VII (2), 140 - 145." type="journal article" year="2015">
Korb 
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF2FFECE57B02E9FBD9FD0E" box="[1089,1146,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">et al.</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
: plate 1 figs 3 &amp; 4). From the photographs of the 
<typeStatus id="8C798804FFF2FFECE0ED028DFD9AFD32" box="[471,569,727,753]" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">holotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation id="CBF92A23FFF2FFECE37D028DFD50FD32" box="[583,755,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–20" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1710,1734]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,381,1687]" captionTargetId="figure-121@9.[151,1436,381,1687]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 17–20. 17, Holotype of Melitaea phoebe abbas, Gross &amp; Ebert, 1975. © R. Trusch. 18, Allotype of Melitaea phoebe abbas, Gross &amp; Ebert, 1975. © Alipanah. 19, Holotype of Melitaea ornata adversaria Korb, Stradomsky &amp; Kuznetsov, 2015. 20, Paratype of Melitaea ornata reliquiae Korb, Stradomsky &amp; Kuznetsov, 2015. Figs 19, 20 © S.K. Korb, B.V. Stradomsky &amp; G.V. Kuznetsov.A = upperside, B = underside, C = labels on specimen pin." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577646" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577646/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">Figs 19 A, B, C</figureCitation>
) it is clear that the specimens figured show the distinguishing characters of the wings and antennae of 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF2FFECE36302A1FD69FCD7" authorityName=", Russell &amp; Tennent" authorityYear="2016" box="[601,714,763,788]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornata">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF2FFECE36302A1FD69FCD7" box="[601,714,763,788]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">M. ornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and not of 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFF2FFECE27302A1FC1CFCD6" box="[841,959,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoebe">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFF2FFECE27302A1FC1CFCD6" box="[841,959,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="35">M. phoebe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
